Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the @smoked paprika{1%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin strips.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1}.

Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the sliced pepper, onion and @British beef mince{240%g}. Fry until the mince has browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{40%g} with a #grater{}.

When the mince has browned, drain and discard any excess fat. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

> IMPORTANT: The mince is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Add the @Caribbean style jerk{1%tsp} and garlic to the mince and fry until fragrant, ~{1%minute}.

Stir the @BBQ sauce{48%g} through the mince until thickened and warmed through, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Taste and season with @salt{} and @pepper{} if needed.

When everything's ready, share the wedges between your #bowls{} and top with the BBQ beef.

Sprinkle over the cheese.

Spoon over the @burger sauce{45%g} to finish - wedges loaded! Enjoy!